 BEFORE THE APPEAL PANEL OF THE PRESS COUNCIL OF SOUTH AFRICA In the matter between: NEWS24                                                                                                                APPLICANT and JURIE ROUX                                                                                                  RESPONDENT Matter No: 9507 DECISION ON AN APPLICATION FOR LEAVE TO APPEAL The above procedure is adopted to avoid the matter being heard in a piece meal manner where there is a dispute about the late filing of the complaint and its condonation. 4.1  The application for leave to appeal is refused. 4.2 The matter is referred back to the Public Advocate to be conducted as set out in paragraphs 2.3 et seq. Dated this 4th day of July 2022. Judge B M Ngoepe, Chair, Appeals Panel 